This paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of linear programming to compute maximal lotteries, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of mathematical optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
